main event: A civilian observed 5 crescent-shaped objects changing color in the sky while stargazing near Milton, Wisconsin on 22 May 1966.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for 1 hour and 25 minutes, Objects appeared at intervals of 56 minutes, with the fifth object appearing 70 minutes after the fourth, The objects did not produce any sound and had an irregular and slow maneuverability, The observer used a telescope for the observation, The observer was located four miles north of Milton, Wisconsin.
